net.grasinga.discord.bots.eNetMusic

Class eNetMusic

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dv8tion.jda.hooks.ListenerAdapter
      • net.grasinga.discord.bots.eNetMusic.eNetMusic
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.dv8tion.jda.hooks.EventListener

    class eNetMusic
extends net.dv8tion.jda.hooks.ListenerAdapter
    eNetMusic is a music bot that brings basic music functionality to Discord. It requires a bot token and bot management role to be passed in. The arguments can be passed from the command line or a bot.properties file in the bot's directory. bot.properties file should have one argument per line. Arguments are as follows: - Bot Token - Bot Management GuildRole (Used to send command errors if any occur.)
    Created by Grasinga using JDA and JDA-Player
    See Also:
    Grasinga's GitHub, JDA, JDA-Player

      • onGuildMessageReceived

        public void onGuildMessageReceived(net.dv8tion.jda.events.message.guild.GuildMessageReceivedEvent event)
        Checks for a command anytime a guild message is received.
        Creates parameters for all functions that run commands.
        Parameters are as follows:
            guild = Guild of the event's message.
            channel = TextChannel of the event's message.
            message = The event's message.
            commandline = The command and arguments of the event's message.
            command = The command of the event's message.
            audioManager = The guild's AudioManager.
        Runs any functions that the command specifies by passing in the above parameters where it's appropriate. (This is the main function that calls all the other functions.)
        If the MusicPlayer is not already created; creates the MusicPlayer via createMusicPlayer(audioManager).
        Overrides:
        onGuildMessageReceived in class net.dv8tion.jda.hooks.ListenerAdapter
        Parameters:
        event - Contains all the info needed for running commands.
        See Also:
        GuildMessageReceivedEvent, Guild, TextChannel, Message, AudioManager

      • playNonRadio

        private void playNonRadio(net.dv8tion.jda.entities.TextChannel channel,
                          java.lang.String commandline)
        Gets a Youtube or SoundCloud video from the given argument. Argument expected is a valid YouTube link, SoundCloud link, or a search term. If the YouTube or SoundCloud link is invalid, the function will assume it is a search term. The search term is then sent to getVideoId(term).

        Link is then passed into addToPlaylist().
        Parameters:
        channel - Used to get the TextChannel the command was entered on.
        commandline - Used to get the arguments of the command.
        See Also:
        getVideoId(String), addToPlaylist(TextChannel, String), onGuildMessageReceived(GuildMessageReceivedEvent)

      • playRadio

        private void playRadio(net.dv8tion.jda.entities.TextChannel channel,
                       java.lang.String commandline)
        Gets a radio station from the given argument. Argument expected is a valid mp3 stream source link or a search term to check for in radioStations. If link is invalid the function assumes it to be a search term. If the search term does not match a station in radioStations, then the default radio station is selected instead.

        Station link is then passed into addToPlaylist().
        Parameters:
        channel - Used to get the TextChannel the command was entered on.
        commandline - Used to get the arguments of the command.
        See Also:
        addToPlaylist(TextChannel, String), onGuildMessageReceived(GuildMessageReceivedEvent)

      • removeFromQueue

        private void removeFromQueue(net.dv8tion.jda.player.MusicPlayer player,
                             net.dv8tion.jda.entities.TextChannel channel,
                             java.lang.String commandline)
        Removes the specified song from the playlist based on the argument provided. If no argument is given, the function will remove the last added song if possible. Valid arguments are: the position of the song in the playlist's queue (number), audio links, or a search term. Sends a message to channel notifying if the song was removed.
        Parameters:
        player - Used to get the current MusicPlayer.
        channel - Used to get the TextChannel to send the message to.
        commandline - Used to get the arguments of the command.
        See Also:
        onGuildMessageReceived(GuildMessageReceivedEvent)
